There&#39;s no need to create `nameList` as an array for this. You can iterate the `propNames` set directly:

    private static void addProperties(Properties prop) {
        Set&lt;String&gt; propNames = prop.stringPropertyNames();
        for (String propName:  propNames) {
            String propertyValue = prop.getProperty(propName);
            allProp.put(propName, propertyValue);
            loadOldValues(propName, propertyValue);
        }
    }

You might also be able to make use of [`allProp.putAll(prop)`][1] rather than iterating through the keys (though this might require restructuring `loadOldValues`).


